tool.summary:
Two or multiple polygons that are connected through a shared point or border may be considered as a single feature. This tool is used to merge (or dissolve) these connected polygons into larger polygons. The tool generates three outputs:

  • a new featureclass after merging connected features that share borders

  • a new featureclass after merging connected features that share points

  • a new featureclass after merging all connected features that share either borders or points

These new featureclasses can then be used as inputs to the AddAttributes toolset and the ClassificationFeatures toolset to generate attributes and assign feature types. Note that this tool can be used for both bathymetric high and bathymetric low features.

The merging processes include:

  • identify those features that are connected through shared points

  • identify those features that are connected through shared borders

  • dissolve (merge) these connected features accordingly

# specify input and output parameters of the tool inFeat = 'po10_1_05std_300000m2_BL' mergedFeatAll = 'po10_1_05std_300000m2_BL_joinedAll' mergedFeatBorder = 'po10_1_05std_300000m2_BL_joinedBorder' mergedFeatPoint = 'po10_1_05std_300000m2_BL_joinedPoint'
# execute the tool with user-defined parameters arcpy.AccessoryTools.Merge_Connected_Features_Tool(inFeat,mergedFeatAll,mergedFeatBorder,mergedFeatPoint)
